>       Question:  Instead of all of these complex password restrictions,
>       wouldn't it be easier to offer the alternative of a really, really
>       long password?  I mean, it would be a pain to login, sure, but it's
>       easier to remember "A step in the right direction, I think." than 
>       it is to remember BB9!dgo.  Of course, I'm not suggesting that you
>       lose the option of a short, complex word.
